sentences: Bernard Francis McGann (22 June 1937 – 17 September 2013) was an Australian jazz alto saxophone player.
He began his career in the late 1950s and remained active as a performer, composer and recording artist until near the end of his life.
McGann won four ARIA Music Awards between 1993 and 2001.

Born in Granville, in Sydney's western suburbs, McGann first came to prominence as part of a loose alliance of modern jazz musicians who performed at the El Rocco Jazz Cellar in Kings Cross, Sydney in the late 1950s and early 1960s.
